main event: On September 6, 1965, an unidentified object was observed in Long Beach, New York, moving from southeast to northwest for roughly 3 minutes.
interesting points: The observer described the object as a bright light that appeared similar to a star,The object had a constant horizontal motion and was captivating enough to draw attention,It was observed under clear skies, allowing for unobstructed visibility,The observer concluded that the object could be a satellite or an illumination flare,Despite the investigation, no physical evidence or photographs were available.
witness description: A civilian observer with prior experience in the military.
